      </p>
      <p>
        I'm a skilled developer who enjoys challenges and isn't afraid to try
        new things.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article
      class="download-cv grid grid-rows-[min-content_1fr] rounded-xl p-6"
    >
      <p class="mb-4 font-semibold text-white">
        If Iâ€™ve caught your attention and youâ€™re interested in my CV, you can
        download it by clicking the button below.
      </p>
      <div class="place-self-center">
        <a
          href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1DNHxV3PoitPLw8ZwpFKZZc5o2dsZ1Z_d/view?usp=drive_link"
          target="_blank"
          class="flex cursor-pointer items-center rounded-md bg-[#FF3B00] p-2 text-white"
          ><FileText class="mr-1" /> Download CV</a
        >
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

  <ContactMe class="mb-8" />
</Layout>

<style>
  /* true */
  .download-cv {
    margin: 0;
    --x: calc(var(--posX, 0) * 1px);
    --y: calc(var(--posY, 0) * 1px);
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(115deg, rgb(211 255 215), rgb(0 0 0)),
      radial-gradient(
        90% 100% at calc(50% + var(--x)) calc(0% + var(--y)),
        rgb(200 200 200),
        rgb(022 000 045)
      ),
      radial-gradient(
        100% 100% at calc(80% - var(--x)) calc(0% - var(--y)),
        rgb(250 255 000),
        rgb(036 000 000)
      ),
      radial-gradient(
        150% 210% at calc(100% + var(--x)) calc(0% + var(--y)),
        rgb(020 175 125),
        rgb(000 010 255)
      ),
      radial-gradient(
        100% 100% at calc(100% - var(--x)) calc(30% - var(--y)),
        rgb(255 077 000),
        rgb(000 200 255)
      ),
      linear-gradient(60deg, rgb(255 000 000), rgb(120 086 255));
    background-blend-mode:
      overlay, overlay, difference, difference, difference, normal;
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  document
    .querySelector('.download-cv')
    .addEventListener('pointermove', (e) => {
      const { currentTarget: el, clientX: x, clientY: y } = e;
      const {
        top: t,
        left: l,
        width: w,
        height: h,
      } = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      el.style.setProperty('--posX', x - l - w / 2);
      el.style.setProperty('--posY', y - t - h / 2);
    });
</script>
